OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGraveyard thefts disrespect
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fthe dead - councillor      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Families visiting loved ones' graves in
OL,6, the run-up to Christmas have been left 
OL,7, upset by thieves breaking into         
OL,8, cemeteries, a councillor has said.     
OL,10,FMetal pipes and taps have been stolen  
OL,11,Ffrom five graveyards in Bridgend       
OL,12,Fcounty, which John Spanswick said      
OL,13,Fshowed "utter disrespect for the dead".
OL,15,FThis has left the cemeteries without a 
OL,16,Fwater supply, causing distress for     
OL,17,Fthose tending graves, he added.        
OL,19,FSouth Wales Police has asked the public
OL,20,Fto report suspicious behaviour.        
